How did Friealtor come to be? Friealtor was an idea that was first thought of during the home crash circa 2008. This was because many people could have sold their homes, if not for the traditional fees and efficient processes associated with real estate. Also of note, many people would have been willing to do somethings on their own to save a lot of money in a real estate transaction process.  Why is happening Friealtor now? Full Description: An industry leading importer of food service supplies, health & wellness products and medical devices, Remcoda, a division of IBrands Global, is a family-run business with extensive experience in product sourcing and manufacturing, logistics, and distribution. The company is known as the USA’s largest importer of safety equipment to the food service and medical industries in 2021. Throughout the pandemic, Remcoda had imported more than 25 million boxes of protective disposable gloves, syringes, medical gowns, N95 masks and touchless thermometers.  Remcoda oversees a global supply chain and has offices, showrooms, and distribution centers throughout the United States, including in Los Angeles, Las Vegas, New York, New Jersey, Baltimore, Houston and Savannah, Georgia. It also maintains offices in Hong Kong and Shanghai.  Founded by Marc Garson and led by CEO Remy Garson, Remcoda owns the proprietary wellness and medical brand BluZen. BluZen is a preeminent protective glove brand that penetrates the healthcare sector through its membership in the Premier GPO. BluZen products have been featured in major media outlets like Bloomberg, CNBC, and Fox Business, and can be found at more than 9,000 retail outlets throughout North America, Latin America, Asia, and Europe. Select U.S. retail locations include Walmart, CVS, Rite Aid, Wayfair, and Bloomingdales. Remcoda also partners with major U.S. food service providers such as Performance Food Group and Aramark.  Remcoda is an adaptable organization that leverages its manufacturing and sourcing experience to address unique global challenges. Recently, it pioneered supply chain solutions to develop eco-friendly, compostable products to address the paper shortages and plastic crisis. These Remcoda products include 100% compostable and biodegradable disposables products ranging from cutlery & straws to hot and cold cups to school lunch trays, pizza boxes, and to-go containers. More recently, in April 2022, IBrands Global announced the creation of Remcoda Express to address global supply chain challenges. This full-service freight and logistics enterprise intends to lower shipping costs by cutting out freight forwarding middlemen and utilizing a fleet of trucks and equipment in addition to ocean shipping carriers. This same division has been assisting with the nationwide ethical disposal of massive overstocks of expired sanitizer, hazardous material built up from the early days of the COVID pandemic.

Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Smart RX Systems is the developer, manufacturer and operator of the Smart PharmAssist™ Kiosk line of remote healthcare technologies and services. The Smart Smart PharmAssist™ Kiosk is a remote pharmacy dispensing technology that allows people to have access to multi-lingual pharmacy services 24-hours a day, seven days a week. Smart PharmAssist™ Kiosk uses remote, scanning and biometric technologies to provide patients with a remote, face-to-face consultation with a pharmacist and to have their prescriptions filled quickly and safely at the kiosk. The Smart PharmAssist™ Kiosk is a complete pharmacy-in-a-box, with the capacity to dispense over 7,500 different prescription and Over the Counter (OTC) medications, and includes features such as pill counting, refrigeration, facial recognition technology, and Biometrics. The Smart PharmAssist™ Kiosk is entirely automated system with override capability to manually control the dispensing of medication by a pharmacist. The Smart PharmAssist™ kiosk puts 24-hour pharmacists and pharmacies everywhere, extending the reach of traditional pharmacies without the time, distance, language, or costs of traditional retail pharmacies. Current Pharmacy’s margins are getting tighter, governments are seeking lower costs and increased accessibility, and the population is aging with a commensurate demand on healthcare resources these are global trends that the Smart PharmAssist™ Kiosk technology was built to mitigate by creating a safe, cost effective remote alternative to the traditional retail pharmacy. Pharmacies, pharmacy-benefit-managers(PBMs), health-maintenance-organizations (HMOs), employers and insurance carriers can now consider labor costs as globally flexible and scalable according to demand. It frees them from being tied to retail locations and allows them to deliver new service and information offerings. Smart RX Systems created a platform to lower their operating costs and allow them to capture more market share.
